                "text": "Now I have a complete picture of the `/src/anylist` directory. Let me provide a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## /src/anylist Directory Structure Analysis\n\n### 1. Directory Tree\n\n```\nsrc/anylist/\n├── claude_code_context/\n│   ├── CLAUD_CONTEXT_README.md\n│   ├── claude_detailed_context.sh\n│   └── claude_full_context.sh\n├── proxy.py\n├── requirements.txt\n└── llm.log\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. File Descriptions\n\n#### `/src/anylist/proxy.py` (Main Application)\nA **FastAPI-based HTTP proxy server** that bridges Claude Code with Alibaba's DashScope API.\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Purpose**: Proxies Anthropic-format API requests to DashScope's backend\n- **Upstream Target**: `https://coding.dashscope.aliyuncs.com/apps/anthropic`\n- **API Endpoint**: `/v1/messages` (Anthropic-compatible)\n- **Authentication**: Converts `x-api-key` header to DashScope's `Authorization: Bearer` format\n- **Logging**: Comprehensive request/response logging via `AppLogger` class\n- **Stream Handling**: Forces all requests to non-streaming mode\n\n**Core Components:**\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `AppLogger` | Custom logger with timestamp, round-counting, and JSON formatting |\n| `build_upstream_headers()` | Transforms headers for DashScope compatibility |\n| `proxy_messages()` | Main endpoint handling `/v1/messages` requests |\n| `proxy_other()` | Catch-all for other Anthropic endpoints |\n\n**Configuration:**\n- Default API Key: `sk-sp-xxx` (via `DASHSCOPE_API_KEY` env var)\n- Runs on: `0.0.0.0:8000`\n\n---\n\n#### `/src/anylist/requirements.txt` (Dependencies)\nPython package dependencies:\n```\nfastapi==0.109.2\nuvicorn==0.27.1\nhttpx==0.26.0\n```\n\n---\n\n#### `/src/anylist/claude_code_context/` (Shell Scripts Directory)\nContains three files for extracting and analyzing Claude conversation context from JSONL session files.\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `CLAUD_CONTEXT_README.md` | Documentation for the context extraction tools |\n| `claude_full_context.sh` | Full conversation context extractor with formatted output |\n| `claude_detailed_context.sh` | Detailed JSON analysis with statistics |\n\n**Shell Script Capabilities:**\n- Parses Claude session JSONL files from `~/.claude/projects/`\n- Formats messages by type (user, assistant, system)\n- Extracts tool call information (`tool_use`, `tool_result`)\n- Displays timestamps and message statistics\n- Uses `jq` for JSON processing\n\n---\n\n#### `/src/anylist/llm.log` (Log File)\nAuto-generated log file created by `proxy.py`'s `AppLogger`. Contains:\n- Request round numbers (第 N 轮)\n- Full request payloads (model, messages, parameters)\n- Response summaries\n- Error details\n\n**Format Example:**\n```\n{2026-03-13 11:22:32}-第 1 轮 - 模型请求完整信息\n{\n  \"请求轮次\": \"第 1 轮\",\n  \"模型\": \"qwen3.5-plus\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Code Organization\n\nThe codebase follows a **simple flat structure** with one main application and supporting utilities:\n\n```\nanylist/\n├── Application Core\n│   └── proxy.py          # FastAPI proxy server\n├── Configuration\n│   └── requirements.txt  # Python dependencies\n├── Utilities\n│   └── claude_code_context/  # Session analysis scripts\n└── Runtime Output\n    └── llm.log           # Request/response logs\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Key Patterns and Architecture\n\n#### Architecture Pattern: API Proxy/Gateway\n```\nClaude Code Client  →  proxy.py  →  DashScope API\n     (Anthropic          (Header          (Aliyun\n      format)          transformation)     backend)\n```\n\n#### Design Patterns Used:\n\n1. **Logger Pattern**: `AppLogger` class encapsulates logging logic with:\n   - Round-based session tracking\n   - JSON pretty-printing\n   - Dual output (file + console)\n\n2. **Header Transformation**: Selective header passthrough with credential mapping:\n   ```python\n   PASSTHROUGH_HEADERS = {\"anthropic-version\", \"anthropic-beta\", \"content-type\", \"accept\"}\n   ```\n\n3. **Request Interception**: Captures and logs all request/response data before forwarding\n\n4. **Stream Conversion**: Forces streaming requests to non-streaming mode for simplified handling\n\n#### Shell Script Patterns:\n- **jq-based JSON processing** for structured data extraction\n- **Template functions** in `claude_full_context.sh` for different message types\n- **Auto-discovery** of latest session files using `ls -t`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Summary\n\nThe `/src/anylist` directory contains:\n\n1. **A FastAPI proxy server** (`proxy.py`) that enables Claude Code to work with Alibaba's DashScope API by translating Anthropic-format requests\n2. **Claude session analysis tools** (shell scripts) for debugging and extracting conversation history\n3. **Comprehensive logging** for monitoring LLM API interactions\n\nThis appears to be a development toolset for running Claude Code with Chinese LLM backends (DashScope/Qwen models) while maintaining full visibility into the API traffic.",
